owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
As per Article 4(11) of the GDPR, consent of the data subject means any freely given, specific, informed and unambiguous indication of the data subjects wishes by which he or she, by a statement or by a clear affirmative action, signifies agreement to the processing of personal data relating to him or her;

In the case of this ontology, 'Consent' is a concept as well as an entity. To separate this distinction with relation to the data subject, the `Consent` class represents the consent of the data subject in its entirely, including any history and annotations for it. The class `ConsentInstance` represents the given consent at a specific time, which is linked to the Consent class.

To link the `Consent` instance with the `DataSubject` instance, use the [`isConsentFor`](#isConsentFor) and [`hasConsent`](#hasConsent) properties.

owl:Class.vann:example:
@prefix gconsent: <https://w3id.org/GConsent#> .
